And since they came to this holy city, persisting in the bond of charity in perfecting and preserving the union of their Society in Christ, and promulgated a certain formulary of life, in accordance to what they have by experience ascertained to be conducive to the end proposed by them, and conformable to evangelica] designs and to the canonical sanctioris of the Fathers; it has come to pass that the manner of life of their associates, contained in the said for- mulary is not only applauded by many good men, zealous towards God ; but is also so much approved by some, that they desire to follow the same.
